"content": "<style>\nh1.thlex-title { font-size: 1.3em; margin: 0 0 0.4em; }\n.thlex-key { color: #888; font-size: 0.85em; font-weight: normal; margin-right: 0.4em; }\nnav.thlex-index { margin: 0.5em 0 0.75em; }\nnav.thlex-index ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2em; }\nnav.thlex-index li { margin: 0.15em 0; font-size: 0.95em; }\n.thlex-section { margin: 0.6em 0; }\nh2.thlex-heading { font-size: 1em; margin: 0.5em 0 0.2em; }\nh3.thlex-subheading { font-size: 0.95em; font-weight: normal; font-style: italic; margin: 0.2em 0; }\n.thlex-language-sets { margin: 0.3em 0 0.3em 1em; }\n.thlex-language-set { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 0.75em; border-left: 3px solid #e0e0e0; }\n.thlex-language { font-size: 0.8em; color: #888; margin-right: 0.4em; }\n.thlex-lemma { font-weight: bold; font-family: serif; }\n.thlex-translit { color: #555; font-style: italic; font-size: 0.9em; margin-left: 0.3em; }\n.thlex-refs { font-size: 0.85em; color: #444; margin-top: 0.15em; }\n.thlex-paragraphs p { margin: 0.35em 0; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.5; }\n.thlex-image { margin: 0.5em 0; display: block; }\n.thlex-image img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }\nfigcaption.thlex-caption { font-size: 0.85em; color: #555; font-style: italic; margin-top: 0.2em; }\n.thlex-abbr { border-bottom: 1px dotted #888; cursor: help; }\n.thlex-xref { color: #1a5fb4; }\nspan[data-bnType=\"bibleReference\"] { color: #1a5fb4; }\ntable.thlex-table { border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.9em; margin: 0.5em 0; }\ntable.thlex-table td { padding: 0.2em 0.6em; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #ddd; }\ntable.thlex-table tr:first-child td { font-weight: bold; background: #f5f5f5; }\nul.thlex-index-list { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.6; }\nul.thlex-index-list ul { margin: 0.1em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; }\n.thlex-index-key { font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; }\n</style><h1 class=\"thlex-title\" id=\"REALIA:1.5.3.1\"><span class=\"thlex-key\">1.5.3.1</span> 標題：線、繩、紗（thread, string, yarn）</h1><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">經文出處</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-sets\">\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">來： חוּט</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： chut)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen14:23\">GEN 14:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh2:18\">JOS 2:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg16:12\">JDG 16:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl4:12\">ECC 4:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song4:3\">SNG 4:3</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">來： פָּתִיל</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： pathil)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen38:18\">GEN 38:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen38:25\">GEN 38:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod28:28\">EXO 28:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod28:37\">EXO 28:37</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod39:3\">EXO 39:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod39:21\">EXO 39:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod39:31\">EXO 39:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num15:38\">NUM 15:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num19:15\">NUM 19:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg16:9\">JDG 16:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek40:3\">EZK 40:3</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">描述</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>\n            <figure class=\"thlex-image\"><img class=\"thlex-img\" src=\"images/OAI-0015_piece_string.png\" alt=\"一根繩子\"><figcaption class=\"thlex-caption\">一根繩子 (Image generated by ChatGPT using OpenAI technology)</figcaption></figure>將纖維在紡錘上旋轉扭繞，就可製成編織所用的線或紗線（參<a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">1.5.3 布料生產 (cloth manufacture)&lt;REALIA:1.5.3&gt;</a> ）。以這種方式製造的單股線不是特別結實，但是把許多條這種細股線交織在一起而製成的布料就非常結實，可做許多用途。另參<a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">1.14 繩、帶 (rope, cord)&lt;REALIA:1.14&gt;</a> 。</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">翻譯</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>「線」與「帶子」或「繩子」之間的根本區別在於其構造，而不是粗細。或者說，繩子是由兩根或多根單股線扭絞或編織而成。這裡列出了所有出現希伯來文<em>pathil</em> 的經文，但是在其中一兩處，翻譯者可能會認為這個詞是指較粗的帶子。</p>\n<p>在<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod39:3\">EXO 39:3</a> 中，希伯來文<em>pathil</em> 是指用金子做成的細「線」（“threads”；<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised Standard Version (1952)\">RSV</abbr> 、<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Contemporary English Version\">CEV</abbr> ）或「縷」（“strands”；<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New International Version (1984)\">NIV</abbr> ）。有些語言可能有一個專門用詞來表示這種由金屬製成的「細絲」。</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
